<DocsLayout title="Content Moderation" description="Configure content moderation in PicFast.">
  <h1>Content Moderation</h1>
  <p>PicFast includes optional content moderation to review images before they become publicly visible.</p>

  <h2>Moderation modes</h2>

  <h3>Disabled (default)</h3>
  <p>All uploads are immediately accessible. No review required.</p>

  <h3>Manual</h3>
  <p>Uploaded images are marked as <strong>pending</strong> and hidden from public feeds. Administrators review them in the admin panel under <strong>Moderation</strong>. Approved images become visible; rejected ones are deleted.</p>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <p>Set the moderation mode in <code>config.yaml</code> or the admin panel:</p>
  <pre><code>app:
  moderation_mode: "manual"  # "" | "disabled" | "manual"</code></pre>

  <h2>Admin review</h2>
  <p>Go to <strong>Admin → Moderation</strong> to see pending images. Approve or reject each one with optional notes.</p>
</DocsLayout>
